					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">iirc emulating the FDS correctly results in non-working games because the game dumps themselves are incorrect (missing GAP sections and some other crucial items).
<br />
<br />Emulators either have to employ hacks or attempt to reconstruct the missing sections in order for it to be operable.
<br />
<br />EDIT:  some related threads I dug up:
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?t=3372">http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?t=3372</a><!-- m -->
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?t=738">http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?t=738</a><!-- m --></div>

