				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">There is no delay on disk insert. There is a switch that is engaged when the disk is set. If it's ejected then you just unset the disk and the BIOS will throw an error.
<br />
<br />The stuff you mentioned about Gaps and CRCs that are missing from the disk really annoyed me when looking at adding FDS support to my emulator. Most games though, atleast official games, use the BIOS for all disk operations. It was easy to just HLE these functions. Works just as well if not better since the time to complete is instant or atleast fully in your control.</div>

