			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Bregalad wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">But since the 6502 ingores the CRC, what's the point to even have the CRC stored on the disc ? Just having it stored on the disc (and ignored by the CPU) won't detect transmission errors. Or is there something I missed ?</div>
<br />The RAM adapter will calculate and verify the CRC. (If $4025 bit 4 is set at the end of file.) The CPU can check whether the RAM adapter detected a CRC error by reading $4032 bit 4 after the CRC has been read.
<br />It will detect errors in stored content on the disk, and errors in retrieval of the file data from the disk.
<br />Checking the CRC error is of course voluntary, but the CPU does not need to calculate it, because the hardware does.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

