					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">_after_ the first CRC byte has already been read (and presumably, accumulated into the CRC sum, rather than verified). How does that work? </div>
<br />Apparently the mathematical structure of CRC is such that appending the correct CRC value to a bitstream will cause the running CRC value to return to the starting value (e.g. $0000 or $FFFF).</div>

